The paper presents a direct brain-to-brain interface for collaborative problem solving using EEG and TMS technologies. The research involves human subjects and focuses on the performance of BrainNet in terms of group-level performance, true/false positive rates, and mutual information between subjects. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves cybernetics (cs.CY) and Systems and Control (cs.SD) as it deals with the integration of multiple brains to solve a task.
